  "commentary": "With SPX at 7106.13 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7111, dealers are in PIN regime and currently long gamma, meaning they're actively selling this rally and providing resistance into the 7110-7115 negative gamma zone where they'll need to buy back hedges. The massive negative GEX walls at 7110 (-10.3B) and 7115 (-8.0B) create amplifying conditions that should cap upside momentum, while the positive gamma support at 7100 (+4.0B) suggests dealers will buy any dips back toward that level. Key inflection points are the flip at 7111 and the major resistance at 7200 (+7.6B) where dealer selling pressure intensifies significantly.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7100-7115 with choppy, range-bound action as dealers fade moves in both directions.",
